From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] branding: redirect update checks to fennec-services

ungoogled-chromium disables Google's update mechanism entirely.
This patch re-enables a minimal update-check mechanism that pings
updates.fennec.computer instead of Google's update servers.

The update check:
  - Is shown in the Request Journal as class kFennecInternal
  - Is disabled by default; enabled only if the user opts in via
    fennec://setup → Services → "Check for browser updates"
  - Sends: Fennec version, channel, platform, OS version
  - Receives: { latest_version, download_url, sha256, release_notes_url }
  - Makes ZERO requests if the user has not opted in

The component updater (for filter lists etc.) is handled separately by
the FilterListManager and also requires explicit user opt-in.

PILLAR: Transparency / Privacy
JOURNAL: logs as kFennecInternal when update check fires; visible in
         the Request Journal sidebar panel.

